Deploy Jetty 8.1.x (using jetty-osgi-boot for web bundle support) to Karaf 3.0.0-SNAPSHOT

Usage(Windows):
   1. Open a DOS console, change the current directory to jetty-on-karaf.
   2. Run "mvn clean install" to build the projects.
   3. Unzip "jetty-on-karaf\apache-karaf\target\jetty-on-karaf-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT.tar.gz".
   4. Open a DOS console.
   5. Change the current directory to be in "jetty-on-karaf-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT".
   6. Run "bin\karaf"
   7. On the Karaf Console, run "feature:install -v karaf-webconsole"
   8. To access the web console, use "http://localhost:8080/system/console/bundles", type "karaf" for username and "karaf" for password.

NOTE: for my enviornment, the local maven repository to located in c:/.m2. If you use the default local maven repository, remove the following line in org.ops4j.pax.url.mvn.cfg before you run "bin\karaf":
    org.ops4j.pax.url.mvn.settings=file:/c:/.m2/settings.xml
